<section id="what-is">
<div class="lang-en">
      <h2>What Is Qi Men Dun Jia?</h2>
      <p>Qi Men Dun Jia (<span class="chinese-char">奇門遁甲</span>, Qí Mén Dùn Jiǎ) is one of the Three Great Divination Arts (<span class="chinese-char">三式</span>) of classical Chinese metaphysics, alongside Tai Yi Shen Shu and Da Liu Ren. Its name translates roughly to "Mysterious Gates Escaping Techniques" &mdash; <em>Qi</em> refers to the three special stems (Yi, Bing, Ding), <em>Men</em> to the eight gates, and <em>Dun Jia</em> to the hiding of the Jia stem within the six Yi stems.</p>
      <p>The system creates a multi-layered chart that maps cosmic energy across <strong>nine palaces</strong> (based on the Luoshu magic square), integrating Heavenly Stems, Earthly Branches, eight gates, nine stars, and eight spirits. By reading the interactions between these layers at any given moment, a practitioner can assess the quality of time and direction for any endeavour.</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
      <h2>何為奇門遁甲？</h2>
      <p>奇門遁甲（<span class="chinese-char">奇門遁甲</span>，Qí Mén Dùn Jiǎ）乃中國古典術數中「三式」（<span class="chinese-char">三式</span>）之首，與太乙神數、大六壬並稱三大絕學。其名稱之義，「奇」指三奇（乙、丙、丁），「門」指八門，「遁甲」則指甲干隱遁於六儀之中。</p>
      <p>此術以<strong>九宮</strong>（源自洛書九宮格）為基礎，構建多層疊合之盤局，融合天干、地支、八門、九星與八神。術者透過解讀各層在特定時刻之交互關係，即可判斷某一時空之吉凶宜忌，為一切行動提供決策依據。</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
      <h2>何为奇门遁甲？</h2>
      <p>奇门遁甲（<span class="chinese-char">奇門遁甲</span>，Qí Mén Dùn Jiǎ）乃中国古典术数中「三式」（<span class="chinese-char">三式</span>）之首，与太乙神数、大六壬并称三大绝学。其名称之义，「奇」指三奇（乙、丙、丁），「门」指八门，「遁甲」则指甲干隐遁于六仪之中。</p>
      <p>此术以<strong>九宫</strong>（源自洛书九宫格）为基础，构建多层叠合之盘局，融合天干、地支、八门、九星与八神。术者通过解读各层在特定时刻之交互关系，即可判断某一时空之吉凶宜忌，为一切行动提供决策依据。</p>
</div>
    </section>

    <section id="origins">
<div class="lang-en">
      <h2>Historical Origins</h2>
      <p>Chinese tradition attributes Qi Men Dun Jia to the <strong>Yellow Emperor</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">黃帝</span>), who reportedly used it to defeat the warlord Chi You at the Battle of Zhuolu. The legendary sage <strong>Jiang Ziya</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">姜子牙</span>) of the Zhou Dynasty is said to have refined it from 4,320 configurations down to 1,080. <strong>Zhang Liang</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">張良</span>), advisor to the founding emperor of the Han Dynasty, further reduced it to the 540 charts (or ju, <span class="chinese-char">局</span>) used in modern practice.</p>
      <p>Historically verifiable texts emerge from the <strong>Warring States period</strong>. Fragments appear in bamboo-slip manuscripts from Mawangdui (c. 168 BCE). By the Tang Dynasty, Qi Men Dun Jia had been systematised into the form recognisable today, with Li Chunfeng producing authoritative compilations. During the Ming and Qing Dynasties, it was classified as a restricted military art, underscoring its strategic significance.</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
      <h2>歷史淵源</h2>
      <p>中國傳統將奇門遁甲之起源追溯至<strong>黃帝</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">黃帝</span>），相傳黃帝於涿鹿之戰中以此術大破蚩尤。周代傳奇謀臣<strong>姜子牙</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">姜子牙</span>）據載將原有四千三百二十局精簡為一千零八十局。漢朝開國謀士<strong>張良</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">張良</span>）再度削減至今日通用之五百四十局（ju，<span class="chinese-char">局</span>）。</p>
      <p>可資考證之文獻始見於<strong>戰國時期</strong>。馬王堆竹簡（約公元前一六八年）中已出現相關殘篇。至唐代，奇門遁甲經李淳風等人整理編纂，已臻體系完備之形態。明清兩朝更將其列為軍事機密，足見其戰略價值之重大。</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
      <h2>历史渊源</h2>
      <p>中国传统将奇门遁甲之起源追溯至<strong>黄帝</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">黃帝</span>），相传黄帝于涿鹿之战中以此术大破蚩尤。周代传奇谋臣<strong>姜子牙</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">姜子牙</span>）据载将原有四千三百二十局精简为一千零八十局。汉朝开国谋士<strong>张良</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">張良</span>）再度削减至今日通用之五百四十局（ju，<span class="chinese-char">局</span>）。</p>
      <p>可资考证之文献始见于<strong>战国时期</strong>。马王堆竹简（约公元前一六八年）中已出现相关残篇。至唐代，奇门遁甲经李淳风等人整理编纂，已臻体系完备之形态。明清两朝更将其列为军事机密，足见其战略价值之重大。</p>
</div>
    </section>

    <section id="structure">
<div class="lang-en">
      <h2>Structure of the Chart</h2>
      <p>A Qi Men chart (<span class="chinese-char">奇門盤</span>) consists of multiple rotating layers superimposed on the nine-palace grid:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Earth Plate (<span class="chinese-char">地盤</span>)</strong> &mdash; The fixed base representing the Luoshu magic square. Each palace corresponds to a direction, trigram, and elemental quality.</li>
        <li><strong>Heaven Plate (<span class="chinese-char">天盤</span>)</strong> &mdash; Nine stars (<span class="chinese-char">九星</span>) rotate atop the Earth Plate. These represent celestial influence and are named after stars of the Big Dipper.</li>
        <li><strong>Human Plate (<span class="chinese-char">人盤</span>)</strong> &mdash; The eight gates (<span class="chinese-char">八門</span>) occupy this layer, representing human activity and intention.</li>
        <li><strong>Spirit Plate (<span class="chinese-char">神盤</span>)</strong> &mdash; Eight spirits or deities (<span class="chinese-char">八神</span>) add a further dimension of cosmic influence.</li>
        <li><strong>Stems Layer</strong> &mdash; The ten Heavenly Stems are distributed across palaces, with the three Qi (Yi, Bing, Ding) representing beneficial forces and the six Yi representing hidden Jia positions.</li>
      </ul>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
      <h2>盤局結構</h2>
      <p>奇門盤（<span class="chinese-char">奇門盤</span>）由多重旋轉層疊合於九宮格之上而成：</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>地盤（<span class="chinese-char">地盤</span>）</strong> &mdash; 固定之底盤，以洛書九宮為基礎。每宮對應一方位、一卦象及一五行屬性。</li>
        <li><strong>天盤（<span class="chinese-char">天盤</span>）</strong> &mdash; 九星（<span class="chinese-char">九星</span>）旋轉覆於地盤之上，代表天象之影響，其名源自北斗諸星。</li>
        <li><strong>人盤（<span class="chinese-char">人盤</span>）</strong> &mdash; 八門（<span class="chinese-char">八門</span>）居於此層，代表人事活動與意志。</li>
        <li><strong>神盤（<span class="chinese-char">神盤</span>）</strong> &mdash; 八神（<span class="chinese-char">八神</span>）構成更高維度之宇宙力量。</li>
        <li><strong>天干層</strong> &mdash; 十天干分布於各宮，其中三奇（乙、丙、丁）代表吉利之力，六儀則藏匿甲干之所在。</li>
      </ul>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
      <h2>盘局结构</h2>
      <p>奇门盘（<span class="chinese-char">奇門盤</span>）由多重旋转层叠合于九宫格之上而成：</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>地盘（<span class="chinese-char">地盤</span>）</strong> &mdash; 固定之底盘，以洛书九宫为基础。每宫对应一方位、一卦象及一五行属性。</li>
        <li><strong>天盘（<span class="chinese-char">天盤</span>）</strong> &mdash; 九星（<span class="chinese-char">九星</span>）旋转覆于地盘之上，代表天象之影响，其名源自北斗诸星。</li>
        <li><strong>人盘（<span class="chinese-char">人盤</span>）</strong> &mdash; 八门（<span class="chinese-char">八門</span>）居于此层，代表人事活动与意志。</li>
        <li><strong>神盘（<span class="chinese-char">神盤</span>）</strong> &mdash; 八神（<span class="chinese-char">八神</span>）构成更高维度之宇宙力量。</li>
        <li><strong>天干层</strong> &mdash; 十天干分布于各宫，其中三奇（乙、丙、丁）代表吉利之力，六仪则藏匿甲干之所在。</li>
      </ul>
</div>
    </section>

